new,SENA Intern,Sutherland,Bogota,2020-02-08,"Job Description
Primary job duties and responsibilities.

1. Inventory related duties: must keep inventory information up to date. GTI interns support us by double checking inventory information every time we require it. They go production floor by production floor checking screens, phones and CPUs serial numbers and asset tags details.

2. Movements and implementations: Considering that we are in a dynamic industry we have some important machines moves constantly. GTI interns help us to perform them by moving screens, CPUs, phones and headsets hen needing to re-accommodate the production floors. They must report to a GTI member what changes have been performed so they can update them on Mainapp.

3. KPIs support: As part of our security compliance, we must keep windows patches and McAfee data base up to date for all site machines. In a daily basis, GTI interns approach to the floor and manually update the mentioned parameters for those machines that for some reason are not able to update them with the automatic mechanisms we have.

4. Warehouse/Storage room organization. Interns help us to keep our warehouse organized and clean. They classify the different kind of elements we have there and they keep the respective inventory up to date.

5. Structured cabling organization: When implementing or moving machines devices cabling requires to be organized and tied. Interns assist us with this.

6. Tickets resolution: As GTI specialists have many things to do in a daily basis, interns assist them by resolving some simple tickets such as peripherals replacing, machines performance issues, machines move, etc.

7. Rename computers: Interns can help renaming computers names in production floor according to the new nomenclature. They have to fill up the file with the new name and the port where it is located.
